#compdef sql-studio
# =============================================================================
# sql-studio — frectonz's "SQL Database Explorer" — a Rust CLI +
#              web UI for browsing SQL databases across 9 backend
#              types: SQLite, libSQL (remote + local), PostgreSQL,
#              MySQL/MariaDB, DuckDB, Parquet files, CSV files,
#              ClickHouse, Microsoft SQL Server.  Distinguishing
#              from DBeaver, DataGrip, dbForge, Adminer, phpMyAdmin
#              by:
#                - SINGLE BINARY + EMBEDDED UI: ships its own
#                  warp-based HTTP server + embedded Svelte
#                  frontend; no external DB tool required
#                - 9 DB BACKENDS via subcommands: sql-studio
#                  sqlite|libsql|local-libsql|postgres|mysql|
#                  duckdb|parquet|csv|clickhouse|mssql
#                - QUERY EDITOR with SQL execution + result tables
#                - SCHEMA BROWSER for tables/columns/indexes/
#                  views/procedures depending on backend
#                - ROW-LEVEL PAGINATION (50 rows per page)
#                - PARQUET + CSV as first-class "databases":
#                  query Parquet files + CSV files with SQL via
#                  DuckDB under the hood
#                - HUMANTIME QUERY TIMEOUT: --timeout flag accepts
#                  "5secs" / "30s" / "1h 30m" / "100ms" style
#                  durations parsed by humantime
#                - AUTO-OPEN BROWSER on startup (--no-browser
#                  disables); --no-shutdown disables shutdown UI
#                - ENV-VAR CLAP: every flag has env-var fallback
#                  via clap(env) — `SQL_STUDIO_TIMEOUT=10s
#                  sql-studio sqlite db.sqlite3` works
#              Used by: developers exploring unfamiliar databases,
#              DBAs auditing schemas, data analysts querying
#              multi-backend warehouses (DuckDB + Parquet + CSV +
#              PostgreSQL from one tool), and as a reference
#              implementation for clap-derive + humantime +
#              warp + multi-backend Rust CLI design.
#
# Author:  frectonz (Frectonz Yvonne) — Belgian/Ethiopian Rust
#          developer who released sql-studio in 2024.  Continuous
#          development through 2026 with regular releases on
#          GitHub.
# Source:  https://github.com/frectonz/sql-studio
#          https://github.com/frectonz/sql-studio/blob/main/src/main.rs
#          https://github.com/frectonz/sql-studio/blob/main/Cargo.toml
# CLI:     src/main.rs — uses clap derive (`#[derive(Parser,
#          Subcommand)]`) with env-var fallback (`#[arg(env)]`)
#          + 9 backend subcommands.  Headline library:
#          **humantime** (clap is well-documented across many
#          Rust completions — humantime is the new variant being
#          documented here, opening Axis 11).
# Library: humantime (https://github.com/tailhook/humantime)
#          ("humantime" — Paul Colomiets (tailhook on GitHub) —
#           released 2017 as a "human-friendly time + duration
#           parser" for Rust.  Two-function API: format_duration
#           + parse_duration.  Distinct from chrono, time-rs,
#           jiff, and other time libraries by being NARROWLY
#           FOCUSED on HUMAN-FRIENDLY DURATION + TIMESTAMP
#           parsing/formatting:
#             1. PARSE FORMATS: "1h 30m" / "30s" / "5days
#                10hours" / "1y 2months 3weeks 4days 5h 6m
#                7s 8ms 9us 10ns"
#             2. FORMAT FORMATS: format_duration(Duration::
#                from_secs(5430)) → "1h 30m 30s"
#             3. RFC 3339 TIMESTAMP parsing/formatting via
#                format_rfc3339 + parse_rfc3339
#             4. NO ALLOC / NO DEPENDENCIES — pure
#                std-library Rust; zero transitive deps
#             5. clap INTEGRATION — humantime::Duration
#                implements FromStr so it can be used directly
#                as a clap-derive field type with `default_value
#                = "5secs"` parsing automatically
#             6. SERDE INTEGRATION via humantime-serde
#                companion crate
#             7. PRECISION: nanoseconds for durations, RFC 3339
#                resolution for timestamps)
# License: MIT (sql-studio); MIT OR Apache-2.0 (humantime)
# Status:  sql-studio — 3,500+ stars on frectonz/sql-studio,
#          rapidly growing; humantime — 600+ stars on tailhook/
#          humantime, ~250M crates.io downloads, foundational
#          dependency of databricks/click + ordinals/ord +
#          cantino/mcfly + svenstaro/genact + racer-rust/racer
#          + andrewchambers/bupstash + alexheretic/ab-av1 +
#          cucumber-rs/cucumber + frectonz/sql-studio (THIS) +
#          yuezk/GlobalProtect-openconnect + tansu-io/tansu +
#          1500+ Rust CLIs needing duration-string parsing.
#
